    The CertName class reflects a complete Name field used in X.509 certificates to define an issuer name or a subject name, or a DistiguishedName field. The difference between Name and DistiguishedName is that Distinguished name is equal to RDNSequence, while Name is a CHOICE, where the only choice is an RDNSequence. As such ,they are equal in practice due to lack of choices for Name. 
     RDNSequence ::= SEQUENCE OF RelativeDistinguishedName
 RelativeDistinguishedName ::= SET SIZE (1..MAX) OF AttributeTypeAndValue

 AttributeTypeAndValue   ::= SEQUENCE {
 type    AttributeType,   -- OID
 value   AttributeValue } -- Any defined by AttributeType
